Titolo: The Palace of Deceit

Anno: 1992

Descrizione: Palace of Deceit is a video game written by Cliff Bleszinski in 1991 in his own company Game Syndicate Productions at the age of 16. The first edition subtitled The Secret of Castle Lockemoer was a text adventure for MS-DOS. On August 31, 1992, it was remade for Windows 3.x and subtitled The Dragon's Plight as a graphical point-and-click adventure game with an entirely new plot and graphics. Both games are played in a first-person perspective and have been released as freeware. Cliff's inspiration came from video games like Déjà Vu and Uninvited.

Genere: Adventure 

Valutazione: N/A
